 <properties>
  <title>Contributing</title>
 </properties>
  <body>
   <section name="Contributing">
    <span class='shortdesc'>Contribute to ${product_name}, either in code, documentation, support, bug reports, improvement requests
     or whatever form you think is useful.</span>

    <p>
      Contributions are very welcome!  
    </p>

<div class='nav'>
 <table>
  <tr>
   <td>Mail</td>
   <td>
     <span class='mail-48 icon-48'/> 
   </td>
   <td>
         <a href="../mail-lists.html">Hippo mailing list</a>:
            The Hippo developers will gladly discuss your
            proposals on the developers mailing list.
   </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td>Issue Tracker</td>
   <td>
     <span class='issue-48 icon-48'/> 
   </td>
   <td> 
          <a href="../issue-tracking.html">${product_name} issue tracker</a>:
                 
          Only Hippo developers and some partners can open issues in the issue tracker, but 
          anyone can contact the developers by email. They are listed as administrators of the Hippo issue
          tracker at the <a href="${issue_tracker_homepage}">Hippo issue tracker homepage</a>, with their
          email adresses (see the bottom of the Login box).
   </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td>Wiki</td>
   <td>
     <span class='wiki-48 icon-48'/> 
   </td>
   <td> 
        <a href="http://${public_project_wiki}">${product_name} wiki</a>:             
        We appreciate contributions of documenation on the public Wiki.
   </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td><a name='forge'/>Forge</td>
   <td>
     <span class='forge-48 icon-48'/> 
   </td>
   <td>
     <a href="http://forge.onehippo.org/">Hippo Forge</a>         
     is a repository filled with all kinds of useful frontend and repository
     plugins. You are very welcome to 
     <a href="http://forge.onehippo.org/account/register.php">sign up</a> 
     and contribute your own plugin, code snippets, etc, for
     all to <a href="../delve_into/sysadmin/installation/plugins.html">install</a>
     and use. 
   </td>
  </tr>
 </table>
</div>

 <subsection name='Alternative'>
   You may also just <a href='./community.html'>use the contributions</a>.
 </subsection>

</section>

